#Text=Canberra Capitals beat Chinese women 's national B basketball team in pre-season
#Text=Saturday , September 29 , 2012
#Text=Belconnen , Australian Capital Territory —
#Text=Michelle Cosier goes for the ball
#Text=Image : Laura Hale .

#Text=Wednesday night , the Canberra Capitals defeated the Chinese women 's national B basketball team 75 – 64 at the Belconnen Basketball Centre in a pre-season warm up game before the start of the Women 's National Basketball League in October .

#Text=Several new players joined the Capitals this season , including Samantha Norwood , Valeria Ogoke , and Tessa Lavey , while Natalie Porter , Carly Wilson , and Marianna Tolo are not with the team this season .
#Text=Playing before a packed crowd , the game started with both teams ' national anthems played , followed by the Capitals giving their guests mini-basketballs .
#Text=Canberra started with Nicole Hunt , Jessica Bibby , Samantha Norwood , Ogoke , and Michelle Cosier on the floor .
#Text=China 's starting lineup included Liang Jiamei , Ma Xueya , Cui Xiaoxue , Huang Hongpin , and Shen Yi .
#Text=The Capitals led early in the first with a score of 6 – 2 and then 6 – 4 , before Jiamei made a three pointer to put China ahead 6 – 7 by the time there was 6:33 left in the first .
#Text=Both teams made a number of substitutions in the first quarter and tried to shoot 3-point shots that they did not land .
#Text=The Capitals could not keep their hands on the ball , turning it over several times in the first .

#Text=Playing a zone defense , the Chinese team appeared to have better control on their side of the court when playing zone defense on that side of the court , while the Chinese offense frustrated the Capitals who were playing man-to-man and appeared to lose the woman they were marking .
#Text=The Chinese were also quick to foul , allowing Canberra to go into bonus .
#Text=The quarter ended 13 – 19 thanks to a last minute shot by Hunt .
#Text=The second quarter started with a Canberra possession , where they turned over the ball to China before they were able to get a shot up .
#Text=Ogoke managed to steal the ball back before China could capitalize on the turnover .
#Text=The Chinese bench started making noise on the bench , cheering and chanting to support their teammates on the court .
#Text=The Capitals coach , Carrie Graf , was very animated on the sidelines .
#Text=Chinese fouls sent Canberra to the line several times , with Norwood scoring a pair with 1:41 left in the half .
#Text=Dombkins made a pair of baskets in the remaining time to bring the score to within two by end of the quarter .
#Text=At the end of the first half , with the score 31 – 33 in favour of China , Norwood led the Capitals in scoring with 11 points and was the only team member in double digits .
#Text=Mikaela Dombkins and Hunt both had 6 points , with six total Capitals players having gotten points on the board .
#Text=On the Chinese side , Sun Mengran led her team in scoring with 12 points .
#Text=Jiamei was second with 5 points , and seven other players also scored .
#Text=Contrasting half time styles saw the Capitals go into the locker room , while China stayed on the court and practice shooting baskets .
#Text=When the second half got under way , Ogoke scored for Canberra to tie up the game .
#Text=China scored to go up again , but Cosier then drew a foul , went to the line and made a pair of baskets to tie the game again .
#Text=Ogoke scored again and the Capitals went ahead by two .
#Text=Bibby quickly added to the lead with another 2 points .
#Text=Following a Chinese time out , China took advantage of a free throw opportunity to narrow the score to 39 – 37 .
#Text=Canberra fell apart a bit , with Cosier turning over the ball and Bibby missing a pass because she was out of position .
#Text=Thee Capitals were not marking players , leaving the Chinese shooters open , but they could not get the ball in the net .
#Text=A 3-point shot by China had them ahead by one .
#Text=With 5:27 left in the third , Canberra was leading by three .
#Text=By the time there was 1:18 left , Canberra led by 53 – 46 with China in foul trouble and the Capitals sitting there with four .
#Text=Four seconds later , Bibby drew a foul and was all smiles before going to the line .
#Text=Once there , she put her game face on and scored a pair of free throws to put the Capitals up by 9 .
#Text=With 50.6 seconds left in the third , Cheng Feng fouled out and sent Bibby to the line again , where Bibby scored another pair of three throws .
#Text=Graf was yelling at her team to push down the court , and Hunt did , scoring 2 points to put her team ahead by 13 .
#Text=With 5 seconds left in the quarter , the Capitals turn the ball over and the quarter ends 59 – 46 .
#Text=Hunt , Bibby , Norwood , Ogoke and Cosier started the fourth for Canberra , while Ma Xueya , Sun Mengran , Jiamei , Shen Yi and Huang Hongpin started for China .
#Text=China continued to play zone defense in this quarter and their bench continued to support their on court players .
#Text=With the Caps ahead 61 – 50 , Graf yelled at Hunt to shoot , and Hunt did , making a 3-point shot .
#Text=Later in the quarter , Hunt shot an airball and Brigitte Ardossi did a good job keeping in play , getting the ball back to Hunt who failed to score on the next shot .
#Text=Hunt would finish the half 2 of 4 from 2 point range .
#Text=With 4:52 left in the game , China took a time out .
#Text=On the bench , Xueya had her fingers buddy taped , despite not starting the game with her fingers that way .
#Text=Following the time out , Graf had to yell at Bibby several times .
#Text=On the next opportunity to bring subs in , Bibby was subbed out of the game .
#Text=China kept trying to score 3 points but was unable to capitalise .
#Text=By the time there was 2:09 left in the game , Hunt was trying to slow play down .
#Text=When Hunt was subbed out , the game sped up again .
#Text=With 24 seconds left , China scored a 3 pointer to bring the score to 75 – 64 where the score remained unchanged in the remaining time .
#Text=The game ended with Jessica Bibby leading in scoring for her team with 16 total points , 1 point ahead of Norwood who had 15 and 2 points ahead of Hunt who had 14 .
#Text=6 of Bibby 's points came from a pair of 3-point shots in the second half .
#Text=The only other player for her team to score a 3 pointer was Hunt .
#Text=Only Tessa Lavey , who played only 2 minutes and 12 seconds and the returning Alice Coddington who played 13 minutes and 56 seconds failed to score for the Capitals .
#Text=Dombkins led her team in rebounding with 8 , while newcomer Ogoke had 7 .
#Text=The Canberra Capitals regular season starts on October 5 , with first home game to be played on October 20 , which will be Lauren Jackson 's first game with the team .
